==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|es|en}} {{m|es|sombrero||hat}}, from {{m|es|sombra||shadow, shade}} + {{m|es|-ero}}, literally, "shade-maker."

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}
[[File:Sombrero (PSF).png|thumb|sombrero]]

# A [[hat]] of a particular kind, with a high conical or cylindrical crown and a saucer-shaped brim, highly embroidered, made of plush felt.
# A mixed drink with [[coffee liqueur]] and [[cream]], named after the hat.
# {{lb|en|bowling}} A series of four consecutive [[strike|strikes]].

